===Etymology===
From the Classical {{der|en|la|perspicuitās||transparency”, “lucidity”, “[[self-evidency]]”, {{sense|in post-Classical Latin}} “penetration”, “insight}}, from {{m|la|perspicuus||clear”, “evident}}; compare {{m|en|perspicacity}} and the {{cog|fr|perspicuité}}.

